    • Method Detail

      • onFetchStarted

        void onFetchStarted()
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has started.

      • onFetchProgress

        void onFetchProgress(long bytesFetched)
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has progressed.

        The progress will only be reported if the Fetcher is capable of monitoring the progress.

        Parameters:
        bytesFetched - Total amount of bytes fetched so far.

      • onFetchSuccedded

        void onFetchSuccedded(Long bytesFetched)
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has succeeded.
        Parameters:
        bytesFetched - Total total amount of bytes fetched or null, if the Fetcher is not capable of monitoring the progress.

      • onFetchFailed

        void onFetchFailed(FetchException exception,
                   Long bytesFetched)
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has failed.
        Parameters:
        exception - The FetchException that caused the process to fail. This is the same FetchException that is thrown in the failing method of Fetcher that this FetchProgressListener has been given to.
        bytesFetched - Total total amount of bytes fetched before the process failed or null, if the Fetcher is not capable of monitoring the progress.

      • onFetchFinished

        void onFetchFinished()
        Indicates that the process of fetching bytes from an InputStream has finished.

        This method will be called after either onFetchSuccedded(Long) or onFetchFailed(FetchException, Long) has been called.
